1.	Create an algorithm to separate digits of a positive integer number and print the digits backward. 
Example:
Input 712
Output 2   1    7


variables

number (input)
chars (number of characters inputed)
x
counter


initialize
counter = 0
chars = number of inputs


process
step 1
number is integer(>0)?
NO - Print "not valid"

YES -Next step

step 2

counter ++ (counter increased by 1)
x = (chars) - (counter)
swap the first char to the right "x" times;  

step 4
char = counter ?

NO - step 2 again

Yes - print number






